# 06 — Documentation Standard

## Document hierarchy

| Layer | Location | Purpose |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Vision / architecture | `docs/000–009` | Official Gen1 specifications |
| Foundation | `docs/PROJECT_*.md`, `ENGINEERING_*.md` | Philosophy, workflow, process |
| SRS | `docs/SRS/` | System requirements (volumes) |
| Decisions | `docs/ADR/`, `docs/EDL/` | Architectural decisions |
| Handbook archive | `docs/handbook/` | v1.0 zip and legacy index |
| Agent context | `.ai/`, `agents_stuff/` | Operational AI context (not official spec) |

## Requirements language

- Atomic, unambiguous, testable requirements use **shall**.
- Avoid vague terms without measurable criteria.
- Use TBD / TBC / ASSUMPTION / OPEN ISSUE for unknowns.

## ADR / EDL

Every approved architectural decision: context, decision, alternatives, consequences, status, date.

Supersede — do not delete — prior decisions.

## Templates

`docs/templates/` — ADR, Requirement, Qualification, Architecture Review, Work Package.

Do not duplicate long spec text; cross-reference `docs/NNN_*.md`.
